I am using iPad mini 16 GB Wi-Fi only model from past 11 months (since Feb 2013). I assume I can give a proper feedback on the product. Delivery from flipkart was as always good, well packed, received on the 2nd day. Product Review - Hardware =========================== 1. As always Apple has built this product keeping user experience as their top priority. 2. Premium build. No other tablet comes even closer to this in terms of build quality (Not even iPad 4, except iPad Air which was launched recently. iPad Air is similar in build to iPad mini). 3. Lightning port is awesome. Its small and faster than the previous ones. 4. 5 MP camera is more than sufficient for a tablet (I guess very very very few people would like to take photos with their tablets). Front camera is also good for video chat. 5. All physical buttons gives good tactile feedback and it won't breakdown after regular use. It will for sure lasts for its lifetime (Except Home button - Please see Useful tips and Apps section below in my review for workaround). 6. Battery is very good. Even after using for close to a year, it is giving me 10 Hrs of back-up. I can easily watch 3 full length English movies easily plus can do few other tasks. 7. Touch sensitivity, I guess no words required. No one can match Apple products on this. Product Review - Software =========================== 1. Apple products always don't have top of the line processors/ RAM available in the market (I mean lot of other tablets might have Quad-core processor and 2 GB of RAM). But They exactly know how to get maximum out of the box. 2. As always Hardware and Software made to work together by Apple. 3. All apps run smoothly without any issues. 4. This came with iOS6 and I've upgraded to iOS7 and this brought in a lot of new features like control centre, new notification centre, viewing/ switching b/w recently used apps etc. Its really good. 5. Compared to Android this is a matured app ecosystem (I liked the Android's Google Play store interface though). You will find less number of bugs/ blind apps. All the apps are always updated quickely to new releases. Few Useful tips and good app suggestion ======================================== 1. Constant use of home button will definitely cause an issue after 1 year or one and a half year. You can address this issue by enabling assistive touch. This acts like a home button plus lot more with iOS7. 2. Few apps which I would suggests are (this is my personal opinion and I am not mentioning games) a. Pocket (To read contents offline) b. NDTV c. Snapseed (photo editing) d. Adobe Reader e. iBooks f. VLC (I guess no need to explain about this :P) g. ESPN Cricinfo h. facebook, gmail and twitter (The usual suspects) i. Chrome j. Google maps Concerns =========== There are not many. But a few 1. Photos and videos look great, there is no doubt about that. But given the pricing, they should have provided Retina display. 2. All the stuff needs to be transferred via iTunes. Some ways this is good since when you are using on a new computer you need to authorize it and some ways it is bad (especially for people who often format their PCs and install fresh copies of Windows). You need to keep a copy of back-up always. 3. Using iTunes is difficult for those who are new to Apple products. This is really not user friendly unless you are very familiar with it. Also transferring via iTunes is time consuming. 4. No memory card slot, means no expansion (like any other Apple products). One good thing about Apple products is that you are guaranteed with regular software upgrades/ updates. You can at least have 2 to 3 OS upgrades (In android you will hardly get OS upgrade, unless you buy their flagship product and even for those you will get only 1 upgrade). Having said that I would highly recommend this product and if you are frequent traveller and want to use internet on the move, you can go for Cellular + Wi-Fi model (Which is little expensive). I would give 8.5/10 for this product.
