The Ipad Mini is what the ipad should always have been. Its feather light and is so easy to carry with you that you may not notice the weight at all. Perfect to read books, surf web, photos, skype among other . Pretty snappy. You won't notice the A5 and the 512MB RAM in daily use. It is as snappy as the bigger ipad. The only minor differences are seen when playing games live Dead Trigger, NOVA etc. Perfect for students with the just perfect screen size and portability. Awesome built and oozes quality. Specially the black version. Compared below to the Nexus 7 Bought both of them from the US in November. Will List Down Some Comparisons: Screen: IPM has lower resolution than the N7 and surely the individual pixels are coarser. But its not noticeable until you kiss the tablets close. On the other hand IPM has FAR BETTER colour saturation. You will surely notice it using them side by side. And lastly, the 0.9" extra screen size and the 4:3 ratio does wonders to the all tablet experience other than watching movies. If you plan to watch movies on a regular basis on a tablet take the N7. Specs and Performance: N7 blows IPM with raw specs but daily use but apple really does have some black magic optimizations with its iOS6 making it as smooth or even smoother than the N7. Half the cores and the RAM bearing IPM is still able to give the N7 a match when it comes to REAL world smoothness. Benchmarks may say otherwise. FEEL in HAND: There is no battle here. IPM takes the lead here and by a LONG margin. The thin profile and just the correct size make it more pleasurable to hold than its rival any day. IT exudes quality which cannot be said about the N7. APPS: Apple optimized maps are too good for the generic android apps. Use Flipboard, Skype and a few other popular apps and you will know what I mean. FLEXIBILITY: Android is the king here. Launchers, Custom ROMS and what not. IF you like to see your baby in a new set of cloths everyday, N7 is it. Apple may look like a boring nerd who never looks any different. But those with limited tech skills should prefer the ipad. CONVENIENCE: Again its Android. No itunes shit. Just simple Drag and Drop. Plus unparalleled codec support. VERDICT: The N& priced at 19.900 in India is a no brainer to get the IPM unless you are a sucker for movies. Its really every inch an ipad for several grands lesser. :)
